 up at the bottom and turns to ice.";i:44;s:126:"You probably wont notice until you try to open the door and the motor and chain start to move but then jerk to an abrupt stop.";i:45;s:91:"If you think that your door is frozen to the ground do not continue to use the garage door.";i:46;s:92:"16 May 2009 at 1149PM edited 30 November -1 at 100AM in In My Home includes DIY MoneySaving.";i:47;s:90:"Ive got an up and over garage door ie as it lifts the top goes in and the bottom goes out.";i:48;s:100:"Its always been a bit stiff when closing it I always need to kick the bottom a bit to get it closed.";i:49;s:52:"Did the usual today but kicked too hard at one side.";i:50;s:197:"A common problem with garage door openers is when the door gets stuck halfway and refuses to close all the way down or closes smoothly but when it gets halfway it reverses and opens all the way up.";i:51;s:129:"Apart from being a big inconvenience such situations are potentially dangerous as the can act as easy access points for burglars.";i:52;s:98:"A common cause of a garage door that wont close or open during cold weather is a frozen threshold.";i:53;s:75:"This event happens when the ground is wet usually from rain and it freezes.";i:54;s:131:"If you believe that your garage door is stuck due to being frozen its important not to try opening it until youve cleared the area.";i:55;s:144:"The metal components of garage door systems tend to contract when very cold which overtaxes the opener especially if your garage isnt insulated.";i:56;s:108:"Your electric door opener is under even more stress if it is confronted with a garage door stuck in the ice.";i:57;s:92:"Another contributing factor to a door frozen shut is a high level of humidity in the garage.";i:58;s:65:"To reduce humidity in this space read the advice in this article.";i:59;s:36:"Try to lift the garage door by hand.";i:60;s:66:"If the door opens smoothly by hand the problem is with the opener.";i:61;s:73:"If the garage door still only opens halfway the problem is with the door.";i:62;s:18:"Identify the wire.";i:63;s:45:"Shut off the power to the garage door opener.";i:64;s:38:"Use a screwdriver to tighten the wire.";i:65;s:67:"Turn the power back on and the door should open and close normally.";i:66;s:98:"An estimated 76 percent of Americans drive to work every day according to a survey from Brookings.";i:67;s:149:"We depend on our cars which is why when the garage door gets stuck in the closed position with your car inside it can cause a huge flood of emotions.";}}